cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper focuses on computer vision applications, specifically hyperspectral image super-resolution. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an unsupervised encoder-decoder architecture, which suggests that it may fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper incorporates physical constraints of HSI and MSI, which may fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper presents experimental results, indicating that it may also fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
